Compare Model Versions

You are here: Salesforce Help
Compare model versions to better understand what's changed between them.

Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.
Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition.

Einstein Discovery stories are now models. Compare model versions to examine the effects of changes on your analysis.

For example, suppose Einstein notifies you that the data in your dataset has changed, and you created a new model version. You can compare the latest version with a previous version to learn more about how changes in your data affected the outcome.

Open a model with multiple versions then click Data Insights. The overview prompts the user with a What Changed? button, including a change summary with the net difference between versions.

Click What Changed? to compare the current version to a previous one. Einstein automatically selects the immediately previous version and compares them side by side.

To compare with a different version, select it from the dropdown list.
title: Comparing Salesforce Analytics Model Versions
